\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to define how the Elko County Information Operations Department receives,
 routes,
 and responds to service-related feedback and grievances.
 It establishes the authoritative definition of service quality under the Department's compliance-enforcement mandate,
 specifies the legitimate channels through which feedback is accepted,
 defines formal grievance pathways for end users and County departments,
 and protects IT personnel from lateral political pressure by decoupling staff performance evaluation from end-user satisfaction with compliance outcomes.
 This policy does not govern employment or personnel matters,
 which are subject to County HR policies and applicable collective bargaining agreements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Information Operations Department personnel.
 It governs service-related feedback,
 grievances,
 and complaints concerning service delivery,
 technical decisions,
 and compliance-enforcement activities conducted by IT Department personnel in the performance of their duties.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy does not govern personnel or employment complaints —
 including allegations of misconduct,
 harassment,
 discrimination,
 or ethics violations —
 which are subject to County HR processes regardless of whether the subject of the complaint is an IT staff member.
 The boundary between service grievances and personnel complaints is addressed in Section 6.5.
\end_layout

