\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 Boundary with HR and Personnel Processes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy governs service-related feedback and grievances only.
 Complaints alleging employee misconduct,
 harassment,
 discrimination,
 ethics violations,
 or other employment-related matters are not service grievances and are not governed by this policy.
 Such complaints shall be directed to the County's Human Resources function and handled in accordance with County HR policies and applicable collective bargaining agreements,
 regardless of whether the subject of the complaint is an IT staff member.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The distinction between a service grievance and a personnel complaint shall be determined by the substance of the allegation,
 not its framing or channel of submission.
 A complaint that characterizes a technically correct and professionally executed compliance action as hostile,
 inappropriate,
 or otherwise objectionable —
 when submitted to HR rather than through the grievance pathways in Section 6.3 —
 remains a service grievance and shall be evaluated as such.
 When a complaint is redirected from the HR channel to the service grievance process,
 the IT Director shall notify HR of the routing decision and its rationale in writing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Conversely,
 a genuine allegation of misconduct —
 including an alleged violation of the Code of Ethics under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 —
 that arises in the context of a service interaction shall not be processed under this policy.
 The IT Director shall route such allegations to HR immediately upon identification.
 Where the allegation is directed against the IT Director,
 the County Manager shall be notified directly and HR shall be engaged by the County Manager.
\end_layout

